# Project 20: Enterprise Secure Static Website Hosting on AWS

A secure, production-grade cloud architecture implementing static website hosting with zero public access to the backend storage, routed exclusively through a Global Content Delivery Network (CDN).

## 🚀 Architectural Overview
This project solves a common corporate security challenge: hosting a high-performance marketing website while ensuring that the underlying data container remains 100% private from the public internet.

- **Storage:** Amazon S3 (Fully Private Bucket, Block All Public Access Enabled)
- **CDN/Edge Routing:** Amazon CloudFront
- **Security Protocol:** Origin Access Control (OAC) with explicit IAM Bucket Policy restriction
- **Entry Routing:** Default Root Object Configuration (`index.html`)

---

## 🛠️ Infrastructure Components & Details

| AWS Resource | Configured Resource Name / ID | Purpose |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Amazon S3** | `mazam-20` | Holds corporate static web assets securely. Public endpoints are blocked. |
| **Amazon CloudFront** | `E34K2IFXHR6065` | Handles global content caching, TLS termination, and secure routing. |
| **Origin Access Control** | Enabled (OAC) | Modern security standard ensuring only valid CloudFront requests read from S3. |

