## 🔒 Security Configuration (IAM Bucket Policy)
To tightly authorize traffic, the following IAM Bucket Policy was applied to the S3 bucket, explicitly granting read access (`s3:GetObject`) only to the dedicated CloudFront Service Principal:

```json
{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": {
        "Sid": "AllowCloudFrontServicePrincipalReadOnly",
        "Effect": "Allow",
        "Principal": {
            "Service": "cloudfront.amazonaws.com"
        },
        "Action": "s3:GetObject",
        "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::mazam-20/*",
        "Condition": {
            "StringEquals": {
                "AWS:SourceArn": "arn:aws:cloudfront::885662727346:distribution/E34K2IFXHR6065"
            }
        }
    }
}
